intention: Clinical Focus: This grouping value set contains diagnoses used to identify patients with acute myocardial infarction.; Data Element Scope: The intent of this data element is to identify patients with a diagnosis of acute myocardial infarction. Using the Quality Data Model, this particular element would map to the Principal Diagnosis attribute for the Encounter category.; Inclusion Criteria: Include codes that identify patients with acute myocardial infarction. This is a grouping of ICD10CM and SNOMEDCT codes.

concept_set_name: [VSAC Bulk-Import test] Chronic Obstructive Pulmonary Disease
concept_set_version_title: [VSAC Bulk-Import test] Chronic Obstructive Pulmonary Disease (v1)
comments: Exported from VSAC and bulk imported to N3C.
intention: Clinical Focus: This value set identifies patients with a diagnosis of chronic obstructive pulmonary disorder (COPD).; Data Element Scope: This value set was intended to map to the QDM data type of diagnosis, but has the potential to be used in additional ways.; Inclusion Criteria: This value set includes acute COPD exacerbations, and end stage COPD. It also includes mild through severe COPD classifications.
limitations: Exclusion Criteria: This value set excludes concurrent infections. It also excludes diagnoses of bronchitis, bronchiolitis, and emphysema.
provenance: Steward: National Committee for Quality Assurance; OID: 2.16.840.1.113883.3.464.1003.102.12.1007; Code System(s): SNOMEDCT,ICD9CM,ICD10CM; Definition Type: Grouping; Definition Version: Latest; Accessed: 2022-01-19 18:06:37

comments: Exported from VSAC and bulk imported to N3C.
intention: Clinical Focus: This value set contains concepts related to a diagnosis of Type II Diabetes.; Data Element Scope: This value set may use Quality Data Model (QDM) category related to Diagnosis.; Inclusion Criteria: Includes only relevant concepts associated with identifying patients who have type II diabetes.
limitations: Exclusion Criteria: Excludes patients who have type I diabetes, gestational diabetes or steroid-induced diabetes.

intention: Clinical Focus: The purpose of this value set is to represent concepts for a diagnosis of  type I diabetes mellitus.; Data Element Scope: This value set may use a model element related to Diagnosis.; Inclusion Criteria: Includes concepts that represent a diagnosis of type I diabetes mellitus, with or without reference to complications and comorbidities.
limitations: Exclusion Criteria: Excludes concepts that represent a diagnosis of gestational, drug-induced and type II diabetes mellitus without mention of type I diabetes mellitus.
